1
00:00:43,178 --> 00:00:46,713
第七封印
THE SEVENTH SEAL

2
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:05,212
【和合本 启示录8:1】
羔羊揭开第七印的时候……
Ad wen the Lamb opened the seventh seal -

3
00:02:05,341 --> 00:02:09,211
天上寂静……
- there was in heaven a silence -

4
00:02:09,348 --> 00:02:13,395
约有二刻
- which lasted about the space of half an hour.

5
00:02:13,521 --> 00:02:19,111
【和合本 启示录8:6】
拿着七枝号的七位天使……
And the seven angels who had the seven trumpets -

6
00:02:19,239 --> 00:02:22,241
就预备要吹
- prepared themselves to sound.

7
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:34,478
- 你是谁？ - 我是死神
- Who are you? - I a Death.

8
00:04:35,362 --> 00:04:39,611
- 你是来取走我魂魄的吗？
- 我已经伴随在你左右很久了
- Have you come to fetch me? - I have long walked at your side.

9
00:04:39,744 --> 00:04:43,197
- 我知道 - 你准备好了吗？
- That I know. - Are you ready?

10
00:04:43,876 --> 00:04:47,163
我的身体已经准备好了 但是我的心却没有
My body is, not myself.

11
00:04:55,104 --> 00:04:59,151
- 等一下 - 你们都这么说
- Wait a moment. - You all say that.

12
00:04:59,277 --> 00:05:03,407
- 但是我不会等的 - 你下象棋，对吗？
- But I leave no respite. - You play chess, don't you?

13
00:05:04,119 --> 00:05:08,950
- 你怎么知道？ - 从画和民歌中知道的
- How do you know? - From paintings and folk songs.

14
00:05:09,085 --> 00:05:13,548
是的，我是个真正的象棋高手
Yes, I'm actually quite a skillful chess player.

15
00:05:13,676 --> 00:05:17,628
- 不会比我强 - 那我们何不比试比试？
- Not more so than me. - Why play chess with me?

16
00:05:17,766 --> 00:05:21,718
- 正有此意 - 很好
- That's my affair. - You are right.

17
00:05:23,359 --> 00:05:26,445
条件是在和你下棋时我得活着
The condition is I live as long as I resist you.

18
00:05:26,573 --> 00:05:29,778
如果我赢了，你就放了我
If I conquer you, you free me.

19
00:05:36,339 --> 00:05:39,626
你执黑
You have black.

20
00:05:39,762 --> 00:05:43,429
再合适不过了，不是吗？
It's most appropriate, not so?

21
00:06:54,887 --> 00:06:59,635
碾碎那些在床第间的叹息
Squeezed twixt the thighs on a bed of sighs

22
00:06:59,771 --> 00:07:03,023
那是成为像我一样的男子汉
That's the only way to be

23
00:07:03,151 --> 00:07:05,940
的唯一方式
For a man like me

24
00:07:11,499 --> 00:07:16,211
我们的君主高高在上 他有一些害羞
Our Lord sits up high He is somewhat shy

25
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:22,014
但是撒旦，你的亲信 确保你不会孤单
But Satan, your crony ensures you won't be Ionely

26
00:07:22,851 --> 00:07:26,981
他们谈到了在Farjestad 发生的一些可怕的事情
They talk of omens and other horrors in Farjestad.

27
00:07:27,108 --> 00:07:30,194
昨晚有两匹马吃掉了另一匹马
Two horses ate one another last night.

28
00:07:30,322 --> 00:07:35,485
墓地里的墓穴被打开了 遗骨到处散落
Graves had been opened in the cemetery and remains scattered about.

29
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:41,748
昨天下午天空中出现了四个太阳
There were four suns in the heavens yesterday afternoon.

30
00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:02,665
你能告诉我去旅馆的路怎么走吗？
Can you tell me the way to the inn?

31
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:30,619
- 他说了怎么走了吗？ - 没有
- Did he indicate the way? - Not exactly.

32
00:08:30,756 --> 00:08:33,462
- 他说了什么？ - 什么也没说
- What did he say? - Nothing.

33
00:08:33,594 --> 00:08:37,012
- 他是哑巴吗？ - 不，不能那么说
- Was he dumb? - No, one can't say that.

34
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:41,557
我得说他非常善言
I'd say that he was extremely well-spoken.

35
00:08:41,691 --> 00:08:47,199
是的，非常善言 但是不得不承认他的话非常严肃
Yes, well-spoken. But the speech he made was dour. I have to say.

36
00:10:18,562 --> 00:10:23,108
早晨好，你吃早饭了吗？
Good morning. Have you had any breakfast?

37
00:10:23,236 --> 00:10:27,651
真不幸，我不能吃草 为什么你不教教我呢？
Unfortunately, I can't eat grass. Can't you teach me?

38
00:10:27,786 --> 00:10:34,160
手头紧了，这些地方的人 对艺术都不感兴趣
Things are tight. People aren't interested in art in these parts.

39
00:11:28,137 --> 00:11:32,517
米亚，起来！ 我必须告诉你我看见了什么
Mia, wake up! I've seen something I must tell you about.

40
00:11:32,644 --> 00:11:36,097
- 出什么事了？ - 我刚才出现了幻觉
- Has something happened? - I've had a vision.

41
00:11:36,234 --> 00:11:40,483
不，不是幻觉，那和真的一样
No, not a vision. It was like it was real.

42
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:44,532
知道了…你又有幻觉了
I see... Have you had another vision?

43
00:11:46,793 --> 00:11:50,080
总之，我看到她了
I saw her, anyway.

44
00:11:50,215 --> 00:11:55,557
- 谁，你看到谁了？ - 圣母玛利亚
- Who? Who did you see? - The Holy Virgin Mary.

45
00:11:57,144 --> 00:12:00,847
- 真的？ - 她近得我都可以摸到她
- Really? - She was so close I could touch her.

46
00:12:00,984 --> 00:12:04,521
她头戴金冠，身上披着蓝色的花衣
She had a crown of gold and a blue dress with flowers -

47
00:12:04,656 --> 00:12:08,490
她赤着脚，皮肤微黑
- and she was barefoot and had small brown hands.

48
00:12:08,621 --> 00:12:12,407
她牵着那个小孩，教他走路
She held the child and taught him to walk.

49
00:12:12,545 --> 00:12:16,759
她看到我看她，还对我笑
Then she saw that I'd seen her and she smiled at me.

50
00:12:16,885 --> 00:12:22,131
我的眼中充满了泪水，当我 擦去它们时，她消失了
I got tears in my eyes and when I wiped them away, she disappeared.

51
00:12:22,269 --> 00:12:26,732
到处都变得非常非常宁静
And it became utterly, utterly quiet everywhere.

52
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:32,023
无论天空还是大地 你能想象吗？
In heaven and on earth. Can you understand that?

53
00:12:33,204 --> 00:12:39,293
- 你出现了幻觉 - 你不相信我，但那是真的
- You have an imagination. -You don't believe me, but it was real.

54
00:12:39,423 --> 00:12:43,838
不是你所说的那种真实 而是另一种
Not your kind of reality, but another reality.

55
00:12:43,972 --> 00:12:50,144
就像你上次说魔鬼用它的尾巴 把我们的马车轮子涂成红色一样
Like when you said the Devil painted our wagon wheels red using his tail.

56
00:12:50,274 --> 00:12:52,647
提那个干什么？
Why bring that up?

57
00:12:52,779 --> 00:12:57,574
- 你的指甲里就有红色颜料 - 对，那次是假的
- Red paint was under your nails. - Yes, that time it was made up.

58
00:12:57,704 --> 00:13:02,416
我那样做是为了要你相信 我所看到的真实景象
I did it so you'd believe in my other visions. The real ones.

59
00:13:02,545 --> 00:13:08,053
控制一下你的幻想吧 不然别人会把你当傻瓜看
Control your visions, or you'll be taken for a fool - which you aren't.

60
00:13:08,179 --> 00:13:12,844
起码到现在，没人知道这些
At least not yet, as far as I know. But one never knows.

61
00:13:13,063 --> 00:13:18,523
我那不是幻想！ 我不可能让圣女来救赎
I didn't ask for my visions! I can't help the Holy Virgin revealing herself -

62
00:13:18,655 --> 00:13:22,441
还有那些天使，魔鬼 喜欢和我呆在一起
- and that angels and devils like to be with me.

63
00:13:22,579 --> 00:13:28,122
我不止一次说过早上我需要睡觉！
Haven't I said it once and for all that I need to sleep in the morning?

64
00:13:28,255 --> 00:13:32,089
我要求你，我请求你 但是一点用也没有
I've asked you, begged you, but nothing helps.

65
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:36,516
所以我现在要说…安静！
That's why I'm now saying... quiet!

66
00:13:47,662 --> 00:13:51,709
米克尔，米克尔，米克尔…
Mikael, Mikael, Mikael...

67
00:14:00,934 --> 00:14:06,358
- 他该过的比我们好
- 米克尔将来会是个伟大的杂技演员
- He should have a better life than us. - Mikael will be a great acrobat.

68
00:14:06,485 --> 00:14:11,066
或许是一个伟大的魔术师 会变最不可思议的戏法
Or maybe a juggler who accomplishes the only impossible trick.

69
00:14:11,202 --> 00:14:15,701
- 什么样的戏法？ - 让一个球悬浮在空中
- What trick is that? - Make one ball remain still in the air.

70
00:14:15,834 --> 00:14:21,508
- 那不可能
- 对我们来说不可能，但他可以
- It's impossible. - For us it is. But not for him.

71
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:25,306
你的白日梦…
You and your fantasies...

72
00:14:26,435 --> 00:14:32,228
我昨晚又作了一首新歌 几乎整晚没睡
I made up a new song last night. I lay awake almost all night.

73
00:14:32,362 --> 00:14:37,572
- 你想听听吗？ - 唱吧，我很想听
- Do you want to hear my song? - Sing it. I'm really curious.

74
00:14:37,704 --> 00:14:45,087
一只鸽子栖息在盛夏的百合上
There sits a dove on the lilly In the midst of summer

75
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:49,466
她唱着赞美基督的美妙歌曲
She sings her fair song of Jesus Christ

76
00:14:49,599 --> 00:14:54,394
天堂如此的欢喜
There is great rejoicing in heaven

77
00:14:56,319 --> 00:15:01,661
- 米亚，你睡着了吗？ - 这歌很美
- Mia, are you asleep? - It was a very beautiful song.

78
00:15:01,786 --> 00:15:06,000
- 我还没唱完呢 - 我只是稍微有点困了
- It's not finished yet. - I'm just going to sleep a little more.

79
00:15:06,127 --> 00:15:10,507
- 你可以晚点再唱剩下的部分 - 你除了睡就是睡
- You can sing the rest later. - You just sleep and sleep.

80
00:15:12,387 --> 00:15:16,968
这个装扮怎么样？ 我就是问问
Is this disguise worthy of an actor? I'm only asking.

81
00:15:17,104 --> 00:15:21,270
- 如果牧师不给钱，我就不干了 - 你演死神吗？
- If the priests didn't pay, I'd refuse. - Are you playing Death?

82
00:15:21,403 --> 00:15:25,949
吓吓那些有钱的体面人
Frighten decent people out of their wits with such nonsense.

83
00:15:26,077 --> 00:15:30,077
- 什么时候？
- 在EIsinore的All Saints节日上
- When are we going to do it? - At the All Saints festival in Elsinore.

84
00:15:30,209 --> 00:15:33,662
就在教堂前的台阶上，还不赖
On the actual church steps. Not bad.

85
00:15:33,798 --> 00:15:38,344
为什么不是些艳舞之类的？
人们喜欢看而且也有意思
Why not something bawdy? People like it and it's funnier.

86
00:15:38,473 --> 00:15:43,138
傻瓜，那里现在瘟疫蔓延
Idiot. There's an evil sickness about -

87
00:15:43,356 --> 00:15:47,652
牧师要宣讲严肃的死亡和信仰的问题
- and priests are preaching grim death and moral bellyaches.

88
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:52,279
- 我们演什么？ - 你们演人的灵魂
- What roles will we play? - You're the human soul, you twit.

89
00:15:52,413 --> 00:15:57,921
- 说真的，那是个坏角色 - 谁决定的？谁是老板？
- Naturally it's a bad role. - Who decides? Who's the manager?

90
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:06,435
你们这些傻瓜，忘掉那些规矩吧 生命的细线是非常脆弱的
You fools, keep this law in mind Life's thread is of the weakest kind

91
00:16:06,562 --> 00:16:10,182
你们会发现生命很短暂
Life is short, you will find

92
00:16:11,486 --> 00:16:16,317
女人们会喜欢我这种打扮吗？ 我就是问问
Will women love me in this costume? I'm only asking.

93
00:16:28,431 --> 00:16:33,179
约瑟夫，别说话 什么也别说
Jof? Stand perfectly still. Don't say anything.

94
00:16:33,315 --> 00:16:38,110
- 我安静的像只老鼠 - 我爱你…
- I'm quiet as a mouse. - I love you...

95
00:17:06,537 --> 00:17:09,872
- 你在画什么？ - 死神的舞蹈
- What are you painting? - The dance of Death.

96
00:17:10,001 --> 00:17:13,787
-那是死神吗？
-是的，他一边跳舞一边带走他们所有人
-That's Death?
-Yes, he dances away with them all.

97
00:17:13,924 --> 00:17:18,803
- 为什么画这些？
- 提醒人们他们就要死了
- Why paint such daubings? - To remind people they will die.

98
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:23,979
- 那不会使他们高兴的
- 为什么总要取悦他们呢？
- That won't make them happier. - Why always make them happy?

99
00:17:24,108 --> 00:17:28,607
- 为何不吓吓他们
- 他们最多闭上眼就行了
- Why not frighten them a bit? - They'll just close their eyes then.

100
00:17:28,741 --> 00:17:34,165
相信我，他们一定会看的 一个头骨远比通奸更有吸引力
Believe me, they'll look. A skull is more interesting than a naked wench.

101
00:17:34,292 --> 00:17:39,752
- 如果吓到他们呢？
- 他们就会越想越害怕
- And if you frighten them? - They'll think and be more frightened.

102
00:17:39,885 --> 00:17:43,422
- 然后扑进牧师的怀抱 - 这我不管
- And rush into the priest's embrace. - Not my business.

103
00:17:43,557 --> 00:17:48,352
- 你只画死神的舞蹈
- 我只是想展示那是怎么样的
- You're just painting Death's dance. - I'm only showing how it is.

104
00:17:48,482 --> 00:17:54,191
- 你会惹恼一些人的
- 那么我会再画些轻松的
- You'll anger certain people. - Then I'll paint something cheerful.

105
00:17:54,325 --> 00:17:58,990
人总是要活命的 至少在瘟疫找到你之前是的
One has to make a living. At least until the plague claims you.

106
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:02,710
瘟疫？可怕的…
The plague? That's horrifying...

107
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:07,172
你可以看到那些病人脖子上的疖子
You should see the boil on the neck of the sick.

108
00:18:07,305 --> 00:18:13,928
看看他们是怎样感染的
See how the body contracts, until his limbs become a rope of madness.

109
00:18:16,112 --> 00:18:20,361
- 看上去糟透了 - 是啊…糟透了
- It doesn't look good. - Yes... It doesn't look good.

110
00:18:20,494 --> 00:18:24,161
他试图撕裂他自己
He's trying to tear the bubo out of his bed.

111
00:18:24,292 --> 00:18:29,420
他咬自己的手 用指甲撕开皮肤
He gnaws at his hands, rips out his veins with his nails.

112
00:18:29,551 --> 00:18:33,467
他的尖叫随处可闻
His scream is heard everywhere.

113
00:18:33,599 --> 00:18:36,637
- 你害怕了吗？ - 害怕？我？
- Are you scared? - Scared? Me?

114
00:18:36,771 --> 00:18:40,985
你不了解我，那些是什么东西？
You don't know me. What nonsense is that you've painted?

115
00:18:41,112 --> 00:18:44,982
那些是说人们认为…
The strange thing is that people see -

116
00:18:45,119 --> 00:18:48,490
瘟疫是上帝降临的惩罚
- the plague as a punishment from God.

117
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:55,427
那些病人一路走一路鞭打自己 以祈求上帝的怜悯
Supplicants trail through the land and whip themselves into God's favour.

118
00:18:55,720 --> 00:19:00,551
- 他们打自己？ - 是的，看上去太糟了
- They beat themselves? - Yes, it's an awful sight.

119
00:19:00,687 --> 00:19:04,557
当他们走过来时你就想躲开
You want to run and hide when they come.

120
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:09,693
能打断一下吗？ 我今天一直在喝水
Have you got any snaps? I've been drinking water all day.

121
00:19:09,827 --> 00:19:15,335
- 我就像只沙漠中的骆驼一样干渴 - 你有些害怕了
- I'm thirsty as a camel in the desert. - You did get a little scared, after all.

122
00:19:44,802 --> 00:19:49,846
我想尽可能坦诚地忏悔 但是我的心空空如也
I want to confess as honestly as I can, but my heart is empty.

123
00:19:51,313 --> 00:19:56,940
空虚就像我面前的一面镜子
And emptiness is a mirror turned to my own face.

124
00:19:57,073 --> 00:20:02,830
我看到了我自己… 我被厌恶和恐惧所俘获
I see myself... and am seized by disgust and fear.

125
00:20:08,008 --> 00:20:13,765
由于我对人民的漠不关心 我已被排斥在社会之外
Through my indifference for people, I've been placed outside of their society.

126
00:20:15,186 --> 00:20:20,646
现在我生活在一个幽灵的世界 我的梦境和思想都被占据
Now I live in a ghost world, enclosed in my dreams and imaginings.

127
00:20:20,779 --> 00:20:25,610
- 不管怎样，你不想死 - 是的，我不想
- Despite that, you don't want to die. - Yes, I want to.

128
00:20:25,746 --> 00:20:29,247
- 你在期待什么？ - 我需要知识
- What are you waiting for? - I want knowledge.

129
00:20:30,545 --> 00:20:35,008
- 你想要保证 - 随便你怎么说
- You want guarantees. - Call it what you like.

130
00:20:39,560 --> 00:20:44,557
仅凭一人的感觉想去 理解上帝的意图真的这么难吗？
Is it so terribly inconceivable to comprehend God with one's senses?

131
00:20:44,694 --> 00:20:51,697
为什么他总藏在半真半假的承诺 和从未实现过的奇迹背后呢？
Why does He hide in a cloud of half-promises and unseen miracles?

132
00:20:51,831 --> 00:20:55,582
当我们缺乏信仰的时候 又如何守信呢？
How can we believe in the faithful when we lack faith?

133
00:20:55,713 --> 00:20:59,665
我们将会怎样，谁会去相信？
What will happen to us who want to believe, but cannot?

134
00:20:59,803 --> 00:21:03,589
难道要相信那些我们 不想也不能相信的事情吗？
What about those who neither want to nor can believe?

135
00:21:03,726 --> 00:21:06,479
为什么我不能杀死心中的上帝？
Why can't I kill God in me?

136
00:21:06,606 --> 00:21:10,273
为何他使我蒙羞？
Why does He live on in me in an humiliating way -

137
00:21:10,404 --> 00:21:14,238
尽管我想要把他从我心中抹去
- despite my wanting to evict Him from my heart?

138
00:21:14,369 --> 00:21:20,208
为什么他总像一个 我无法摆脱的嘲笑者？
Why is He despite all, a mocking reality I can't be rid of?

139
00:21:20,337 --> 00:21:24,717
- 你在听吗？ - 我在听
- Do you hear? - I hear you.

140
00:21:24,845 --> 00:21:30,721
我需要真理！不是信仰 不是承诺，而是真理
I want knowledge! Not faith, not assumptions, but knowledge.

141
00:21:30,855 --> 00:21:36,731
我希望上帝能伸出他的手 露出他的脸，和我说话
I want God to stretch out His hand, uncover His face and speak to me.

