00:44:09,883 --> 00:44:14,179
人们都疯狂了，他们逃往内地 把瘟疫也带了过去
People are crazy. They flee inland and take the plague with them.

298
00:44:14,307 --> 00:44:20,349
如果真的是那样，我们 真该庆幸我们还能站着的日子
If it's as they say, then we'll have to enjoy life as long as we're standing.

299
00:44:20,484 --> 00:44:24,484
很多人都死了
Many people have cleaned themselves by fire and died.

300
00:44:24,616 --> 00:44:30,159
但是牧师说死了总好过活在地狱
But the priest says it is better to die clean than to live for hell.

301
00:44:30,292 --> 00:44:35,881
这是末日，我们都知道 只是不敢这样说罢了
This is the end, that's what it is. We all know it, but no one dares to say it.

302
00:44:36,011 --> 00:44:39,881
这是末日，人们因为恐惧而疯狂
This is the end. People are crazy with fear.

303
00:44:40,017 --> 00:44:43,768
- 你也怕了吗？ - 你说的太对了，我怕！
- And you're scared too? - Too right I'm scared!

304
00:44:44,790 --> 00:44:47,911
审判日的黄昏
Judgement Day edges toward evening.

305
00:44:48,045 --> 00:44:54,716
天使降临，坟墓敞开 那真是可怕的景象
The angels descend and the graves open. It will be terrible to see.

306
00:44:58,563 --> 00:45:02,397
- 这个手镯便宜卖你 - 我买不起
- I'll sell you this bracelet cheaply. - I can't afford it.

307
00:45:02,528 --> 00:45:06,943
- 这是纯银的
- 是很漂亮，但是恐怕太贵了
- It's genuine silver. - It's nice, but probably too expensive.

308
00:45:07,077 --> 00:45:11,706
- 你们看到过我妻子吗？ - 她失踪了吗？
- Have you gentlemen seen my wife? - Is she lost?

309
00:45:11,835 --> 00:45:15,621
他们说她和一个演员跑了
She's run away, they say. With an actor.

310
00:45:15,758 --> 00:45:19,211
一个演员？
如果她的品味这么差，就随她去好了
An actor? If she has such bad taste, let her go.

311
00:45:19,348 --> 00:45:24,476
你说的很对 我刚还想杀了她
You are absolutely right. I was thinking I would kill her.

312
00:45:24,606 --> 00:45:30,066
- 我知道，可杀人是另一回事了 - 我还要杀了那个演员
- I see. Murder is another thing. - I'm going to kill the actor, too.

313
00:45:30,199 --> 00:45:33,700
- 演员？ - 那个把她拐跑的家伙
- The actor? - The one she's run off with.

314
00:45:33,830 --> 00:45:37,877
- 为什么？ - 你有毛病吗？
- What for? - Are you thick?

315
00:45:38,004 --> 00:45:43,214
哦，那个演员！我知道 他们现在应该已经走很远了
Oh, the actor! Now I understand. There are far too many of them.

316
00:45:43,346 --> 00:45:47,642
就算他没错，你也要杀他？
Even if he's blameless, you should kill him.

317
00:45:48,146 --> 00:45:53,773
- 你在给他讲故事吗？ - 我？讲故事？
- Are you telling tales to him? - Me? Am I telling tales?

318
00:45:58,288 --> 00:46:03,582
你也是演员，说不定你和他同谋
You're also an actor and it's your cronie that's snuck off with his wife.

319
00:46:03,839 --> 00:46:07,044
你也是演员吗？
Are you an actor as well?

320
00:46:07,178 --> 00:46:10,631
我，演员？不是
Me, an actor? Not really.

321
00:46:10,851 --> 00:46:13,937
那我们会杀了你
Then we should kill you. It's logical.

322
00:46:15,275 --> 00:46:19,061
- 你很有意思 - 你死定了
- You're funny. - You've gone pale.

323
00:46:19,198 --> 00:46:25,454
- 你不会觉得良心不安吗？ - 你很有意思，不是吗？
- Something on your conscience? - You're funny. Don't you think so?

324
00:46:26,669 --> 00:46:32,426
或许我们该在你的脸上 做个坏人的记号
Maybe we should mark you as one does with petty villains of your kind.

325
00:46:33,263 --> 00:46:37,345
你对我妻子干了什么？
What have you done to my wife?

326
00:46:49,666 --> 00:46:53,536
你想杀了我吗？为什么？
Do you want to hurt me? Why?

327
00:46:53,672 --> 00:47:00,177
我在这里碍事吗？ 我最好还是走，不会再来了
Have I annoyed anyone or been in the way? I'll leave and never come back.

328
00:47:00,308 --> 00:47:03,726
站起来，让所有人都能听到你
Stand up so everyone can hear you.

329
00:47:06,652 --> 00:47:09,773
大声点…
Speak louder...

330
00:47:09,908 --> 00:47:15,118
倒立，让我们看看你是不是好演员
Stand on your head so we can see whether you're a good actor.

331
00:47:25,100 --> 00:47:28,553
你对我妻子做了什么？
What have you done to my wife?

332
00:47:30,484 --> 00:47:34,354
- 别想跑，起来跳舞 - 我不，我不
- Don't whimper. Get up and dance. - I can't. I won't.

333
00:47:34,491 --> 00:47:37,446
- 学狗熊的样子 - 我不会模仿
- Imitate a bear. - I can't imitate a bear.

334
00:47:37,579 --> 00:47:40,831
让我们看看
We'll see if you can anyway.

335
00:48:38,682 --> 00:48:43,561
- 起来，当头好熊 - 我不会演熊
- Get up. Be a good bear. - I can't be a bear anymore.

336
00:49:01,178 --> 00:49:04,596
记着下次我们再见到你 会狠狠的收拾你
Remember what I'd do to you if we met again?

337
00:49:06,770 --> 00:49:09,856
我是个守信用的人
I'm a man of my word.

338
00:49:33,189 --> 00:49:36,441
- 他叫什么？ - 米克尔
- What's his name? - Mikael.

339
00:49:36,862 --> 00:49:40,280
- 他多大？ - 刚满一岁
- How old is he? - He's just over one year.

340
00:49:41,370 --> 00:49:46,794
- 他看起来比实际年龄大些 - 你这么想吗？他是挺大的
- He's big for his age. - You think so? Yes, he is quite big.

341
00:49:47,088 --> 00:49:52,049
- 你今天表演了 - 你认为那很糟糕吗？
- You were in a performance today. - Did you think it was bad?

342
00:49:52,180 --> 00:49:56,928
你没化妆看起来更漂亮 这件衣服很适合你
You're more beautiful without make-up. That dress suits you better.

343
00:49:57,063 --> 00:50:03,069
你这么想吗？乔纳森离开了 所以现在我们的情况真是糟
You think so? Jonas Skat went and left us, so now we're in a real fix.

344
00:50:03,198 --> 00:50:07,280
- 他是你丈夫吗？ - 乔纳森？不是
- Is that your husband? - Jonas? No.

345
00:50:07,413 --> 00:50:11,627
- 我丈夫叫约瑟夫 - 哦，他
- The other man is. His name is Jof. - Oh, him.

346
00:50:11,754 --> 00:50:17,262
现在只有我和他 我们还得演出，真是无聊
Now it's only me and him. We'll have to do tricks again, and that's a bother.

347
00:50:17,389 --> 00:50:22,184
- 你也演出吗？ - 哦，是的，而且约瑟夫很会变戏法
- Do you do tricks as well? - Oh, yes. And Jof is a good juggler.

348
00:50:22,313 --> 00:50:26,313
- 米克尔将来还会是个杂耍演员吗？ - 约瑟夫这样希望
- Will Mikael also be an acrobat? - Jof wants him to be.

349
00:50:26,445 --> 00:50:29,650
- 但是你不想？ - 我不知道
- But not you? - I don't know.

350
00:50:29,784 --> 00:50:33,914
- 或许他会是个骑士 - 那可不太好玩，要我说的话
- Maybe he'll be a knight. - It's not so much fun, I can tell you.

351
00:50:34,041 --> 00:50:37,127
- 你看来不高兴 - 没有
- You don't look happy. - No.

352
00:50:37,255 --> 00:50:42,597
- 你很累吗？为什么？
- 我已经厌倦了我的同伴
- Are you tired? Why? - I have boring company.

353
00:50:42,723 --> 00:50:45,975
- 你是说你的随从？ - 不，不是他
- Do you mean your squire? - No, not him.

354
00:50:46,103 --> 00:50:50,150
- 那你说的是谁？ - 我自己
- Who do you mean, then? - Myself.

355
00:50:50,277 --> 00:50:53,980
- 哦，我知道了 - 你真的知道吗?
- Oh, I understand. - Do you really?

356
00:50:54,117 --> 00:50:57,072
是的，我非常理解
Yes, I understand quite well.

357
00:50:57,205 --> 00:51:02,451
我常常想为什么人们总是折磨自己
I often wonder why people torment themselves as soon as they can.

358
00:51:03,007 --> 00:51:08,135
- 米亚… - 约瑟夫…约瑟夫，怎么了？
- Mia... - Jof... Jof, what is it?

359
00:51:09,017 --> 00:51:15,225
约瑟夫！约瑟夫！你怎么了？ 你…快点坐下吧
Jof! Jof, what have you done? Have you...? Come and sit down.

360
00:51:15,361 --> 00:51:19,112
你去哪了？让我看看
Where have you been? Let me look at you.

361
00:51:24,877 --> 00:51:30,634
为什么你非去酒馆不可？ 你喝醉了
Why did you have to go to the tavern? You drank, of course.

362
00:51:30,761 --> 00:51:36,304
- 我没有喝多 - 你老是说什么天使魔鬼之类的
- I didn't drink a drop. - You boasted about angels and devils.

363
00:51:36,438 --> 00:51:41,399
- 人们不喜欢太多的想法 - 我没有提起天使啊
- People don't like too many ideas. - I didn't mention angels.

364
00:51:41,529 --> 00:51:45,825
那么你唱歌跳舞了 你总是表演
Then you sang and danced. You always have to perform.

365
00:51:45,954 --> 00:51:50,001
- 然后他们就生气了 - 你看…
- People get angry at that, too. - Look at what...

366
00:51:50,127 --> 00:51:54,542
看看…看看我给你带什么来了？
Look at what... at what I bought for you.

367
00:51:57,890 --> 00:52:02,934
- 你买不起的 - 反正我弄到了
- You couldn't afford that. - Well, I did it anyway.

368
00:52:03,066 --> 00:52:05,605
约瑟夫！
Jof!

369
00:52:05,737 --> 00:52:11,031
- 哦，他们出手真重 - 为什么你不回手？
- Oh, they gave me such a beating. - Why didn't you give one back?

370
00:52:11,162 --> 00:52:15,494
我只会害怕和生气 但不会很久
I just got scared and angry, but never got that far.

371
00:52:15,628 --> 00:52:20,340
我生气了，相信我 我像狮子一样咆哮…
I got angry, believe me. I roared like a lion...

372
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:24,684
- 他们害怕了？ - 没有，他们都在笑
- Did they get scared? - No, they just laughed.

373
00:52:28,942 --> 00:52:32,479
米克尔…米克尔
Mikael... Mikael.

374
00:52:40,461 --> 00:52:43,333
- 他身上的味道很好闻 - 而且他很结实
- Smell how good he smells. - And he's solid.

375
00:52:43,467 --> 00:52:47,087
你是个棒小伙 绝对是个杂耍演员的料
You're a solid one, you are. A real acrobat's body.

376
00:52:48,433 --> 00:52:52,184
这是我丈夫，约瑟夫
This is my husband, Jof.

377
00:52:53,817 --> 00:52:56,392
- 你好 - 你好
- Good day. - Good day.

378
00:52:56,530 --> 00:52:59,948
你有个很可爱的儿子 他带给你们很多乐趣
You have a fine son. He will bring you joy.

379
00:53:00,078 --> 00:53:04,826
是的，他很可爱 我们有些什么可招待的，米亚？
Yes, he is lovely. Do we have anything to offer, Mia?

380
00:53:04,961 --> 00:53:08,581
- 谢谢，不需要了 - 我摘了些野草莓
- Thanks, I shan't have anything. - I picked wild strawberries.

381
00:53:08,717 --> 00:53:13,013
- 而且还挤了些牛奶 - 有牛奶…
- And we actually milked some milk. - Have milked...

382
00:53:13,141 --> 00:53:16,975
如果骑士大人能和我们 一同进餐那真是荣幸万分
If the knight would join us it would be an honour.

383
00:53:17,106 --> 00:53:21,188
- 请坐吧，我去拿吃的 - 请…
- Sit down and I'll bring the food. - Please...

384
00:53:23,283 --> 00:53:25,692
- 您要去哪？ - 去EIsinore
- Where are you heading? - To Elsinore.

385
00:53:25,871 --> 00:53:29,871
- 我劝你最好别去 - 为什么呢？
- I'd advise against a trip like that. - Why, if I may ask?

386
00:53:30,003 --> 00:53:35,000
瘟疫已经从海岸蔓延过来 上万人因此死掉了
The plague is going down the coast. People are dying in their ten thousands.

387
00:53:35,136 --> 00:53:40,929
- 祸不单行啊 - 跟着我穿过树林
- Trouble always brings his brother. - Follow me through the woods.

388
00:53:41,063 --> 00:53:45,609
你可以呆在我这或者去东海岸 那样就安全了
You can stay at my estate or follow the east coast. You'll be safer.

389
00:53:46,155 --> 00:53:49,442
这些是木草莓，长在山上
They're wood strawberries. They grow on the hill.

390
00:53:49,577 --> 00:53:53,957
我从没见过这么大的 闻上去真香
I never seen them so big. Smell how fragrant they are.

391
00:53:55,671 --> 00:54:00,051
- 请用吧 - 非常感谢
- Enjoy the fare. - I thank you respectfully.

392
00:54:00,345 --> 00:54:04,131
我想你的建议很好，但我还要考虑一下
I think your suggestion is good, but I must consider first.

393
00:54:04,269 --> 00:54:07,307
能有同伴一起穿过树林应该很好
It would be nice to have company through the wood.

394
00:54:07,441 --> 00:54:11,821
我听说那里充斥着幽灵，魔鬼和小偷
It's full of ghosts, devils and thieves. So I heard.

395
00:54:11,948 --> 00:54:15,449
我想那是不错，不过我必须考虑
I said it wasn't bad, but I must consider it.

396
00:54:15,579 --> 00:54:19,116
斯卡离开后，我就是剧团的负责人
Since Skat left, I'm responsible for the troupe.

397
00:54:19,252 --> 00:54:27,169
- 我是老板了 - 我是老板
- I've become the manager, after all. - "I've become the manager, after all."

398
00:54:30,521 --> 00:54:34,022
- 你喜欢草莓吗？ - 他救了我的命
- Would you like strawberries? - That man saved my life.

399
00:54:34,152 --> 00:54:39,909
- 坐下和我们一起吧 - 约瑟夫骑士很慷慨
- Sit down and join us. - The knight's Jons conveys his thanks.

400
00:54:41,664 --> 00:54:44,916
- 哦，这可真好 - 只是短暂的
- Oh, it's so nice. - For a short while.

401
00:54:45,045 --> 00:54:49,710
总是这样，每天都很相似
Almost always. One day is much like the next.

402
00:54:49,845 --> 00:54:54,177
没什么奇怪的 夏天总是好过冬天
Not so strange. Summer is better than winter -

403
00:54:54,311 --> 00:54:59,106
因为你不会受冻 但是春天是最好的
- because you don't freeze. But spring is the very best.

404
00:54:59,236 --> 00:55:02,737
我写了一首有关春天的诗 我去取我的鲁特琴
I wrote a poem about spring. I'll fetch my lute.

405
00:55:02,867 --> 00:55:07,081
别这样，约瑟夫，也许我们 的客人不喜欢你的诗
Not now, Jof. Our guests might not be entertained by your verses.

406
00:55:07,207 --> 00:55:10,328
- 拜托，我自己写歌 - 你说的对
- Please. I write songs myself. - There you are.

407
00:55:10,463 --> 00:55:15,044
我有首有关一条不贞节的鱼的歌 你们一定没有听过
I have one about an unchaste fish you may not have heard.

408
00:55:15,179 --> 00:55:18,051
你们也听不到
You won't hear it, either.

409
00:55:18,184 --> 00:55:23,063
很多人不理解我的艺术 我也不想折磨任何人
Some people don't appreciate my art and I don't wish to torment anyone.

410
00:55:27,157 --> 00:55:31,738
- 烦恼总是这么多 - 当你结婚后会好很多
- One worries so much. - It's better when you are a couple.

411
00:55:31,874 --> 00:55:34,627
- 你有爱过谁吗？ - 是的…
- Don't you have anyone? - Yes...

412
00:55:34,753 --> 00:55:37,958
- 她现在在干什么？ - 我不知道
- What is she doing now? - I don't know.

413
00:55:38,092 --> 00:55:41,795
你看起来很严肃 她是你的甜心吗？
You look so solemn. Was she your sweetheart?

414
00:55:41,932 --> 00:55:47,226
我们是新婚，在一起玩，一起笑
We were newlyweds, played together, laughed quite a lot.

415
00:55:47,358 --> 00:55:53,863
我写歌赞美她的眼睛，鼻子 和美丽的耳朵
I wrote songs to her eyes, her nose, her exquisite, small ears.

416
00:55:53,994 --> 00:55:59,371
我们去打猎，晚上跳舞 生活得非常充实
We went on hunts. In the evening we danced, the house was full of life.

417
00:55:59,503 --> 00:56:03,206
你还要些草莓吗？
Would you like some strawberries?

418
00:56:03,343 --> 00:56:06,429
信仰是沉重的负担，你知道吗？
Faith is a heavy burden, do you know that?

419
00:56:06,557 --> 00:56:12,765
就像一个躲在黑暗中的爱人 无论你怎样呼唤，都不会出现
It's like loving someone in the dark who never comes, no matter how you call.

420
00:56:14,779 --> 00:56:20,821
但是当我坐在这
和你和你丈夫一起时 所有这些都变得虚幻了
But all of that seems unreal when I sit here with you and your husband.

421
00:56:20,956 --> 00:56:24,659
它突然变得无关紧要
It's suddenly insignificant.

422
00:56:24,796 --> 00:56:28,843
你现在看起来不那么严肃了
Now you don't look so solemn.

423
00:56:29,011 --> 00:56:34,720
我会记住这一刻，这祥和的黄昏…
I will remember this moment. The stillness and the dusk...

424
00:56:34,854 --> 00:56:38,474
还有野草莓和牛奶
The bowl of wild strawberries, of milk...

425
00:56:39,946 --> 00:56:43,317
你在暮色中的脸庞…
Your faces in the evening light...

426
00:56:43,452 --> 00:56:48,580
米克尔在安睡，约瑟夫弹着鲁特琴
Mikael lying asleep, Jof with his lute.

427
00:56:48,711 --> 00:56:52,378
我会竭力记住我们说的每句话
I will try and remember what we spoke of.

428
00:56:52,759 --> 00:56:56,510
我会小心地珍藏这段记忆
And I will carry this memory between my hands...

429
00:56:56,641 --> 00:57:01,935
就像捧着满满一碗牛奶一般小心
...as carefully as if it were a bowl brimming with freshly milked milk.

430
00:57:07,367 --> 00:57:13,658
这会是我生命中闪光的一刻…
And this will be a sign for me... and greatly fulfilling.

431
00:57:47,810 --> 00:57:51,347
我一直在等
I have been waiting.

432
00:57:51,482 --> 00:57:54,900
对不起，我有事耽误了
Excuse me, I was somewhat delayed.

433
00:57:55,030 --> 00:57:58,650
我已经调整了战术
As I've given away my strategy, I will retreat.

434
00:57:58,786 --> 00:58:02,406
随便，该你走了
Go ahead. It's your move.

435
00:58:02,584 --> 00:58:06,370
- 为什么你看起来这么开心 - 那是我的秘密
- Why do you look so pleased? - That's my secret.

436
00:58:06,508 --> 00:58:10,888
事实上，我要吃掉你的骑士了
Naturally. I will take your knight now.

437
00:58:11,015 --> 00:58:14,635
当然
You were right to.

438
00:58:14,771 --> 00:58:19,270
- 你在骗我？ - 当然，你掉进了陷阱
- Have you tricked me? - Of course, you fell into the trap.

439
00:58:19,404 --> 00:58:22,656
我控制了局势
I put you in check.

440
00:58:22,785 --> 00:58:27,913
- 你在笑什么？
- 没什么，想办法保你的国王吧
- What are you laughing at? - No matter. Save your king instead.

441
00:58:28,044 --> 00:58:33,587
- 你太骄傲了 - 我们的游戏很有趣
- You are quite arrogant. - Our game amuses me.

442
00:58:33,720 --> 00:58:36,888
该你走了，快点，我赶时间
It's your move. Be quick, I'm in a hurry.

443
00:58:37,017 --> 00:58:43,059
我知道你忙，但是你逃不了比赛
I know you are busy, but you won't avoid our game. It will take its time.

444
00:58:43,319 --> 00:58:47,105
你会和小丑一起穿越树林？
You're travelling with the jesters through the woods?

445
00:58:47,243 --> 00:58:51,195
那个叫约瑟夫和米亚的… 还有一个小孩？
The two called Jof and Mia... who have a little son?

446
00:58:54,880 --> 00:58:58,417
你为什么问这个？
Why do you ask?

447
00:58:58,553 --> 00:59:01,176
没什么…
No reason...

448
00:59:09,697 --> 00:59:14,741
- 你看到乔恩了吗？我们该走了 - 我想他在旅馆
- Have you seen Jons? We must go. - I believe he's in the inn.

449
00:59:18,253 --> 00:59:22,549
天哪，这不是铁匠吗？
Good heavens. If it isn't Plog the blacksmith.

450
00:59:22,677 --> 00:59:25,596
- 晚上好 - 你自己一个人在哭？
- Evening. - Are you snivelling all alone?

451
00:59:25,724 --> 00:59:31,267
是啊，就像一只无助的小兔子
Yes, the blacksmith's sobbing and wailing like a soaked rabbit.

452
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:34,237
- 还是因为老婆？ - 是的，我找不到她
- Still the wife? - Yes, I haven't found her.

453
00:59:34,363 --> 00:59:37,615
是啊，有女人是地狱没有她们还是地狱
Yes, it's hell with women and hell without them.

454
00:59:37,744 --> 00:59:41,079
最好就是趁最好的时候杀掉她们
Logical to kill them when it's at its best.

455
00:59:41,208 --> 00:59:45,457
- 洗洗涮涮 - 大哭的孩子和湿盘子
- Henpecking and swills. - Screaming babies and wet nappies.

456
00:59:45,590 --> 00:59:50,551
- 尖尖的指甲和怨毒的叫骂 - 丈母娘就像魔鬼的姑母
- Sharp nails and malice. - The Devil's aunt as mother-in-law.

457
00:59:50,682 --> 00:59:55,181
- 什么时候才能入睡… - 另一个世界…
- Then when you're going to sleep... - Another tune...

458
00:59:55,315 --> 00:59:59,018
眼泪，诉苦，和满肚子的牢骚
Tears, complaints and laments by the sackfull.

459
00:59:59,155 --> 01:00:02,692
- 为什么你不吻我？ - 为什么你不唱歌？
- "Why don't you kiss me?" - "Why don't you sing?"

460
01:00:02,827 --> 01:00:07,575
- 为什么你不再像以前那样爱我？ - 为什么你不看看我的新衣服
- "Why don't you love me like before?" - "Why don't you eye my new shift?"

461
01:00:07,711 --> 01:00:11,378
- 你只会转过身去打呼噜 - 哦，见鬼…
- "You just turn your back and snore." - Oh, hell...

462
01:00:11,509 --> 01:00:16,672
哦，见鬼…她走了！高兴点！
Oh, hell... She's gone now! Be happy!

463
01:00:18,687 --> 01:00:22,058
我要用我的火钳夹住他们的鼻子
I'm going to pinch them in the nose with my pliers.

464
01:00:22,193 --> 01:00:26,145
我要用我的锤子砸碎他们的胸膛
I'm going to pound them on the chest with the little hammer.

465
01:00:26,283 --> 01:00:31,707
我要砸烂他们的脑袋
I'm going to crack them lightly on the head with the sledgehammer.

466
01:00:31,834 --> 01:00:35,750
看看，他振作起来了！
Look, he's blubbering again!

467
01:00:35,883 --> 01:00:39,717
- 或许我爱她 - 或许你爱她？
- Maybe I love her. - Maybe you love her?

468
01:00:39,848 --> 01:00:44,144
听着，你这笨蛋 爱只是性欲的另一种说法
Listen, you moron, love is another word for lust -

469
01:00:44,272 --> 01:00:50,111
只是欲望加上无休止的谎言和欺骗
- plus lust, plus lust, plus a lot of deception, falsehoods and trickery.

470
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:56,246
- 但是真的很伤人 - 爱是最可怕的瘟疫
- But it hurts anyway. - Love is the blackest of all plagues.

471
01:00:56,375 --> 01:01:00,707
如果沉溺其中或许会有欢乐 但是稍纵即逝
If you died from it there'd be some joy. But it almost always passes.

472
01:01:00,841 --> 01:01:05,553
- 不，我的还没有消失 - 哦，你的也消失了
- No, mine won't pass. - Oh, yes, yours too!

473
01:01:05,683 --> 01:01:10,264
只有少数几个傻瓜才会为爱而死
There are only a few poor dullards now and then who die of love.

474
01:01:10,399 --> 01:01:15,313
如果在这个不完美的世界上 所有的东西都是不完美的
If all is imperfect in this imperfect world, then love is most imperfect -

475
01:01:15,449 --> 01:01:19,496
那么爱就是最不完美的
- in it's perfect imperfection.

476
01:01:19,623 --> 01:01:25,879
你真幸运――能相信这些废话
You're lucky to have such a fluid tongue that you believe your own twaddle.

477
01:01:26,008 --> 01:01:29,842
相信？谁说的 我只不过喜欢给出好建议
Believe? Who said I did? But I love giving good advice.

478
01:01:29,973 --> 01:01:34,436
要求一个却得到两个 我是个好学的青年
Ask for one and you get two. So I'm actually a learned chap.

479
01:01:34,564 --> 01:01:38,398
乔恩，我能和你一起穿过树林吗？
Jons! Can I follow you through the woods?

480
01:01:38,529 --> 01:01:44,487
我太孤独了，也不想回家听他们嘲笑我
I'm so Ionely and don't want to go home as they all laugh at me.

481
01:01:44,665 --> 01:01:48,581
除非你别再哭了，否则我们不会带你
As long as you don't sob all the time or we'll leave you.

482
01:01:48,713 --> 01:01:51,502
乔恩
Jons!

483
01:02:00,650 --> 01:02:04,317
- 我的小兄弟… - 小心，乔恩！
- My little brother... - Watch out, Jons!

484
01:02:04,448 --> 01:02:07,735
- 他只想打架 - 他在哭
- He just wants to fight. - He's sobbing now.

485
01:02:07,870 --> 01:02:13,828
我如果伤到你，我很抱歉 但是我就是这个脾气
I'm really sorry if I harmed you, but I have such a temper.

486
01:02:13,964 --> 01:02:16,836
抓住我的手
Take my hand.

487
01:02:19,223 --> 01:02:23,223
- 让我拥抱你吧，小兄弟 - 等等吧
- Let me embrace you, little brother. - A little later, maybe.

488
01:02:23,354 --> 01:02:27,650
我们真的很忙，谢谢
We're actually in a hurry. Thanks.

489
01:03:17,612 --> 01:03:23,986
啊，我看到了谁？ 谁在森林的边缘若隐若现…
Ah, what do I see? Who is it looms out of the edge of the forest -

490
01:03:24,123 --> 01:03:28,039
如果不是我最爱的演员还会是谁！
- if not My Most Treasured with attached actor!

491
01:03:50,209 --> 01:03:51,752
小心！
Watch out!

492
01:03:51,879 --> 01:03:58,550
你肯定就是那个伤害 我的Kunigunda的脏铁匠
You must be the dirty blacksmith that humiliated my beloved Kunigunda.

493
01:03:58,890 --> 01:04:04,647
- 你叫她什么？ - Kunigunda，你聋了吗？
- What did you say her name was? - Kunigunda. Are you deaf?

494
01:04:04,775 --> 01:04:08,941
她叫莉萨，笨莉萨 小偷莉萨，或者妓女莉萨
Her names's Lisa. Lisa Daft or Sloven or Tart.

495
01:04:09,074 --> 01:04:13,489
- 轻佻的莉萨 - 哦上帝，他真粗鲁
- Drawerless Hussy or Arse Lisa. - Goodness, he's base!

496
01:04:13,532 --> 01:04:18,874
总好过色情，不像你 你这个贱女人
Just good at sleaze, not unlike yourself, you gilded bawd-pudding.

497
01:04:19,083 --> 01:04:22,370
- 天哪，他太过分了
- 你这个恶心丑陋的臭杂种
- Oh, he's base! - You awful, cropped bastard...

498
01:04:22,505 --> 01:04:26,375
如果我是你
...of seven mangey mongrels, if I were in your infested rags -

499
01:04:26,512 --> 01:04:29,930
我就会因为羞愧去撞墙
- I'd be afflicted by such boundless shame -

500
01:04:30,060 --> 01:04:34,689
我会因为自己生的 如此恶心而自甘堕落
- that I'd free nature from my embarrassing countenance.

501
01:04:34,943 --> 01:04:40,237
- 小心点，你这个… - 娘娘腔
- Watch out, you perfumed... - Powder-puff.

502
01:04:40,369 --> 01:04:44,665
娘娘腔… 我会让你死得很难看
Powder-puff... that I don't let off a fart -

503
01:04:44,793 --> 01:04:48,745
送你去杂耍人的地狱
- that will assign you to the juggler's inferno in a flash -

504
01:04:49,759 --> 01:04:53,426
- 在那你们可以坐在一起… - 自言自语…
- where you can sit together and... - Read soliloquies...

505
01:04:53,557 --> 01:04:58,899
自言自语直到魔鬼耳朵都长茧子
Read soliloquies to one another until dust forms in the Devil's ears.

506
01:04:59,150 --> 01:05:03,862
小心点，我会捅破你的肠胃 让它们从你的耳朵流出来
Careful I don't poke your belly so your intestines flow out your ears.

507
01:05:04,951 --> 01:05:12,002
我会痛扁你，让你再不能表演 那些乱七八糟的东西
Careful I don't smack you so you can't even play for Turks and cannibals.

508
01:05:12,130 --> 01:05:15,216
你在笑什么？这很严肃
What are you lauging at? This is serious.

509
01:05:15,344 --> 01:05:19,724
在南方有一种长的很像人的动物叫猿
In southern lands there is a man-like animal called an ape.

510
01:05:19,851 --> 01:05:22,889
- 那又怎么了？ - 只是…
- What of it? - Just that...

511
01:05:23,190 --> 01:05:27,605
- 普洛戈，我的普洛戈 - 什么？
- Plog, my only Plog. - What?

512
01:05:27,740 --> 01:05:31,610
- 什么？ - 亲爱的普洛戈，原谅我吧
- What? - Darling Plog, forgive me everything.

513
01:05:31,746 --> 01:05:37,336
- 她会在一分钟内开始哭
- 我不得不哭，这简直太可怕了
- She'll start crying in a minute. - I have to cry. It's awful.

514
01:05:37,464 --> 01:05:41,416
那个男人欺骗了我，你不会相信的
That man deceived me so badly, you won't believe.

515
01:05:41,680 --> 01:05:47,888
- Kunigunda，如果真相大白的话… - 现在好戏上演了
- Kunigunda, if the truth will out... - And now for his favourite dishes.

516
01:05:48,024 --> 01:05:51,940
普洛戈，我们回家后我给你做饭…
Plog, when we get home I'll make dumplings for you -

517
01:05:52,072 --> 01:05:56,820
做你最爱吃的甘蓝团子
- with mashed turnips and lingonberries which is your favourite.

518
01:05:56,955 --> 01:06:02,415
- 不是吗，普洛戈？
- 是，但是我必须先杀了他
- Isn't that so, Plog? - Yes, but I have to kill him first.

519
01:06:02,548 --> 01:06:06,299
对，杀了他，他真该死
Yes, kill him. Kill him really properly.

520
01:06:06,429 --> 01:06:12,019
- 我一点都不喜欢他
- 上帝啊，为什么你要创造女人
- I don't like him at all anymore. - God, why did you give us woman?

521
01:06:12,147 --> 01:06:15,684
你知道他吗？假胡子和假牙
You know what he is? Just a false beard, false teeth -

522
01:06:15,820 --> 01:06:19,606
假笑和预演好的台词，一个绣花枕头
- false smiles, rehearsed intonation and empty as a jar.

523
01:06:19,743 --> 01:06:22,069
- 杀了他 - 我亲爱的普洛戈
- Go ahead and kill him. - My dear Plog...

524
01:06:24,627 --> 01:06:28,793
如果你以为那就是所谓的我
那你就错了
If you thought I'd defend my so-called reality you're mistaken.

525
01:06:28,925 --> 01:06:33,590
- 杀了我吧，我谢谢你 - 你在说什么？
- Kill me. I'll thank you... afterwards. - What are you saying?

526
01:06:34,143 --> 01:06:37,763
他开始混乱了，已经胜利了一半
He's created confusion. Already a half victory.

527
01:06:37,899 --> 01:06:42,979
- 做点什么，别光站在那 - 我恐怕杀不了他
- Do something, don't just stand there! - He has to fight or I can't kill him.

528
01:06:43,116 --> 01:06:46,487
他必须激怒我才行
He has to provoke me so I get angry like before.

529
01:06:46,830 --> 01:06:51,376
亲爱的朋友，我要把这匕首刺进胸膛
Dear friend, I lower this dagger to my breast.

530
01:06:51,505 --> 01:06:56,051
那样我的形象就会完全改观
And my reality will quickly transform into a new, solid reality.

531
01:06:56,179 --> 01:06:59,466
我的尸体会说明一切
The absolute manifestation of the corpse.

532
01:06:59,602 --> 01:07:02,937
等等…我不是那个意思
Wait... I didn't mean it like that.

533
01:07:03,066 --> 01:07:08,859
我原谅你，Kunigunda，再会了 我的朋友们，时常想想我吧
I forgive you, Kunigunda. Farewell, my friend, pray for me sometime.

534
01:07:25,479 --> 01:07:28,565
哦，天哪…
Oh, dear... Oh, dear...

535
01:07:28,692 --> 01:07:32,395
我真的不是那个意思 我已经开始喜欢他了
I didn't mean it like that. I started to really like him.

536
01:07:32,532 --> 01:07:37,576
他绝对死了，我从没见过这样的死法
He's absolutely dead. I've almost never seen such a dead actor.

537
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:42,463
真是伤心啊 尽管他只是一点小小的要求
It's really sad, although he wanted it himself, poor thing.

538
01:07:42,591 --> 01:07:48,300
- 而我却和她结婚…
- 可是你的小莉萨回来了
- And I'm married to her... - Well, you got your little Lisa back.

539
01:07:48,934 --> 01:07:54,062
- 你不开心吗？ - 乔恩，准确的说…
- Aren't you happy? - Jons, in the strictest confidence...

540
01:07:54,193 --> 01:08:00,235
- 生命是不是太…
- 是的，不过别想它了
- Isn't life quite... - Yes, it is. But don't think about it.

541
01:08:01,497 --> 01:08:05,544
真是疯狂，那就是为什么
It's mad, that's what it is.

542
01:08:12,390 --> 01:08:17,767
表演精彩极了 我如果不是演员就什么也不是了
That was a good performance. I'm nothing if not a good actor.

543
01:08:20,738 --> 01:08:24,785
我会找棵树爬上去
I'll find a tree and climb it.

544
01:08:24,911 --> 01:08:28,958
那样就没有熊，狼 或者幽灵能抓到我了
So no bears, wolves or ghosts can get hold of me.

545
01:08:48,910 --> 01:08:54,999
我明天要去找约瑟夫和米亚 我们一起去All Saints节
I'll find Jof and Mia tomorrow, then we'll go to the All Saints Festival.

546
01:08:56,214 --> 01:09:02,172
我会为自己唱首歌
I'll sing a song to myself. "I'm a little bird who sings how I want"

547
01:09:04,895 --> 01:09:07,981
森林里的工匠…真好啊
Craftsmen in the forest... How nice.

548
01:09:14,328 --> 01:09:17,533
天哪，这是我的树 你居然锯它！
By God, it's my tree they're sawing down!

549
01:09:17,666 --> 01:09:21,796
嘿，你这个混蛋！ 你干嘛锯我的树？
Hey, you dozy cockerel! What are you doing to my tree?

550
01:09:22,216 --> 01:09:26,512
你不会回答吗？
礼貌真是不值钱，你是谁？
Can't you answer? Courtesy is cheap. Who are you?

551
01:09:27,934 --> 01:09:31,637
我锯倒树的时候，你的大限就到了
I'm sawing down your tree as your time is up.

552
01:09:31,773 --> 01:09:36,770
- 这不可能，我没时间 - 你没时间吗？
- It's not possible. I don't have time. - Haven't you got time?

553
01:09:37,366 --> 01:09:42,956
- 我要去演出
- 因为死亡，它已经被取消了
- I've got a performance. - It's cancelled. Because of a death.

554
01:09:43,084 --> 01:09:45,873
- 我的合同！ - 取消了
- My contract! - Annulled.

555
01:09:47,299 --> 01:09:52,296
- 我的家人和孩子…
- 斯卡特，你该感到羞愧
- My family and my children... - Shame on you, Skat!

556
01:09:52,558 --> 01:09:56,095
我是很羞愧，羞愧…
I am ashamed, I'm ashamed...

557
01:09:56,231 --> 01:10:01,311
没有什么特赦之类的？ 一些有关演员的特别规定？
Aren't there any acquittals? Any special rules for actors?

558
01:10:01,448 --> 01:10:04,320
不，没有
No, not in this case.

559
01:10:05,121 --> 01:10:08,373
没有漏洞，没有例外
No loopholes, no exceptions...

560
01:10:53,243 --> 01:10:57,243
月亮从云后升起来了
The moon just came out from behind the clouds.

561
01:10:57,375 --> 01:11:00,662
很好，我们可以更清楚地看路了
Good. We'll see the road better.

562
01:11:01,006 --> 01:11:05,635
- 我不喜欢今晚的月亮 - 森林太安静了
- I don't like the moon tonight. - The trees are so still.

563
01:11:05,931 --> 01:11:12,733
- 那是因为没有风 - 他是说它太寂静了
- That's because there isn't any wind. - He means they are very still.

564
01:11:13,277 --> 01:11:15,769
完全的寂静
It's completely quiet.

565
01:11:16,783 --> 01:11:20,154
- 起码我们能听到狐狸的声音 - 或者是猫头鹰
- If we at least heard a fox. - Or an owl.

566
01:11:20,372 --> 01:11:25,618
或者除了我们之外的人的声音
Or a human voice. Beside one's own...

567
01:11:53,803 --> 01:11:56,805
- 你去哪？ - 找个树桩
- Where are you going? - To the stake.

568
01:11:56,933 --> 01:12:01,562
我知道，是那个巫婆 为什么要在午夜烧死她？
I see, it's the witch. Why burn her in the middle of the night?

569
01:12:01,691 --> 01:12:06,570
- 人们现在都很缺少娱乐 - 安静点
-People lack amusement nowadays. - Quiet, by all the dev... saints.

570
01:12:06,700 --> 01:12:11,780
- 她身体里有魔鬼
- 那你们可是八个勇敢的小伙子
- She has the Devil with her. - Then you men are eight brave men.

571
01:12:11,917 --> 01:12:17,591
我们有酬劳，是自愿干这个的
Well, we're paid. The task was voluntary.

572
01:13:54,589 --> 01:13:58,174
你听得到吗?
Do you hear me?

573
01:13:58,303 --> 01:14:02,968
- 他们说你为魔鬼工作 - 你为什么问这个？
- They say you worked with the Devil. - Why do you ask that?

574
01:14:03,103 --> 01:14:08,397
不是好奇，是很私人的原因
Not out of curiosity, but for highly personal reasons.

575
01:14:08,529 --> 01:14:12,778
- 我也想见见他 - 为什么？
- I also want to meet him. - Why?

576
01:14:14,080 --> 01:14:17,035
我想问问他有关上帝的事
I want to ask him about God.

577
01:14:17,168 --> 01:14:21,084
他一定知道的，如果他是魔鬼
He must know. He if anyone.

578
01:14:22,302 --> 01:14:26,634
- 只要你想你就能见到 - 怎么样做？
- You can see him when you want. - How?

579
01:14:26,768 --> 01:14:29,854
那你就必须照我的话做
But then you must do as I say.

580
01:14:31,692 --> 01:14:35,145
看着我的眼睛
Look into my eyes.

581
01:14:36,576 --> 01:14:40,623
你看到了什么？你看到他了吗？
Well? What do you see? Do you see him?

582
01:14:41,000 --> 01:14:45,914
我看到你眼睛里有一点点恐惧
I see a rigid fear in your eyes.

583
01:14:46,467 --> 01:14:49,719
别的没什么了
Nothing else.

584
01:14:49,848 --> 01:14:53,978
没有人，什么都没有…
No one, nothing... no one...

585
01:14:54,981 --> 01:14:56,773
不…
No...

586
01:14:58,237 --> 01:15:02,569
他不也站在你的身后吗？
Isn't he standing behind your back either?

587
01:15:03,663 --> 01:15:07,366
不，那什么也没有
No. There's nothing here.

588
01:15:10,674 --> 01:15:16,882
但他总是伴随着我 我只需要伸出手就能感觉到他
But he's with me everywhere. I only need to put out my hand and I feel his.

589
01:15:17,018 --> 01:15:21,350
他现在还和我一起，火伤害不了我
He with me now as well. The fire won't hurt me.

590
01:15:21,484 --> 01:15:24,522
- 他这么说的吗？ - 我知道
- Has he said so? - I know.

591
01:15:24,656 --> 01:15:29,819
我知道，你肯定会在某处看到他
I know, I know. You must see him somewhere, you must!

592
01:15:29,957 --> 01:15:33,827
牧师也可以看到他，这些人也可以
The priest had no trouble seeing him, nor the troops.

593
01:15:33,963 --> 01:15:38,177
他们很怕他，他们甚至不敢碰我
They're so scared of him they don't even dare to touch me.

594
01:15:43,229 --> 01:15:46,231
- 为什么你们夹她的手？ - 不是我们干的
- Why have you crushed her hands? - It's not us.

595
01:15:46,359 --> 01:15:50,110
- 谁？ - 问那边的僧侣吧
- Who? - Ask the monk over there.

596
01:15:51,994 --> 01:15:55,661
你对那女孩做了什么？
What have you done to the girl?

597
01:15:59,256 --> 01:16:02,674
你总是不停地发问吗？
Do you never cease asking?

598
01:16:02,803 --> 01:16:06,885
是的…从不停止
No... I never cease.

599
01:16:07,186 --> 01:16:09,595
但是你得不到回答
But you don't get any answer.

600
01:16:27,011 --> 01:16:32,221
我想过杀了守卫 但是没用的，她快死了
I thought about killing the guard, but it doesn't help. She's almost dead.

601
01:16:32,353 --> 01:16:35,938
我告诉你小心点！别离她太近
I told you to watch out! Don't go near to her.

602
01:16:46,543 --> 01:16:50,543
吃了这个，痛苦就会消失了
Eat this and the pain will go.

603
01:17:50,167 --> 01:17:54,630
- 她看到了什么？你知道吗？ - 她不会再有痛苦了
- What's she see? Can you answer? - She's not in pain anymore.

604
01:17:54,758 --> 01:17:59,173
你没有回答我的问题 谁来照顾那些孩子？
You're not answering my question. Who will take care of that child?

605
01:17:59,308 --> 01:18:04,056
是天使，上帝，撒旦
还是什么人都没有？
Is it the angels or God or Satan or just emptiness?

606
01:18:04,191 --> 01:18:07,644
- 没有人，先生… - 不能这样！
- Emptiness, Sire... - It can't be so!

607
01:18:07,780 --> 01:18:12,741
看看她的眼睛
她可怜地意识到一些东西
Look at her eyes. Her poor consciousness is perceiving something.

608
01:18:13,081 --> 01:18:16,748
- 月下的虚无 - 不…
- Emptiness under the moon. - No...

609
01:18:16,879 --> 01:18:21,378
我们只能无能为力的站在这里 看着她看到的一切
We stand powerless with hanging arms, as we see what she sees.

610
01:18:21,511 --> 01:18:24,549
我们和她有着同样的恐惧
Our fear and hers are the same.

611
01:18:24,683 --> 01:18:29,182
那小孩…我受不了了…受不了了
That little child... I can't be bothered, I can't be bothered...

612
01:19:44,359 --> 01:19:49,270
He sings so beautifully of Jesus Christ

613
01:19:49,406 --> 01:19:54,780
There is great joy in heaven

614
01:19:56,170 --> 01:20:02,342
黎明就要来了 尽管有那见鬼的火刑架
The dawn will break soon. Yet the heat hangs like a damp blanket.

615
01:20:02,472 --> 01:20:05,391
我好怕
I'm so scared.

616
01:20:05,519 --> 01:20:10,480
我们知道有些事会降临
但不知道是什么
We feel something is going to happen to us, but we don't know what it is.

617
01:20:10,986 --> 01:20:14,571
- 或许是末日 - 末日
- Maybe the final day. - The final day.

618
01:20:24,300 --> 01:20:28,466
你有水吗？能给我些吗？
Haven't you got any water? Can you give me some water?

619
01:20:31,229 --> 01:20:35,229
- 我染上了瘟疫
- 就在树桩那边别过来！
- I've got the plague. - Keep to the other side of the stump!

620
01:20:41,371 --> 01:20:46,998
我害怕死亡，我不想死，不想死！
I'm scared of dying. I don't want to die, I don't want to!

621
01:20:52,306 --> 01:20:57,350
你们不能可怜可怜我？帮帮我…
Can't you take pity on me? Help me...

622
01:20:57,481 --> 01:21:01,101
至少和我说话！
At least talk to me!

623
01:21:05,787 --> 01:21:10,582
没用的，没用的
It doesn't help. It doesn't help.

624
01:21:10,711 --> 01:21:13,749
我知道那没用
I know it doesn't help at all.

625
01:21:16,930 --> 01:21:20,764
我要死了，我…我…
I'm going to die. I... I...

626
01:21:24,651 --> 01:21:30,325
我将会怎么样？
你们就不能安慰我一下？
What's going to happen to me? Can't you even comfort me?

627
01:21:30,453 --> 01:21:36,162
你们没有一点怜悯之心吗？
你们难道看不到我…
Haven't you got any mercy? Can't you see that I...

628
01:21:36,296 --> 01:21:39,963
没人帮我吗？我不能有点水吗？
Is there no help? Can't I have any water?

629
01:21:41,012 --> 01:21:45,891
毫无意义，那毫无意义
It's meaningless. It's completely meaningless.

630
01:21:46,021 --> 01:21:49,189
我说了那毫无意义
I said it's meaningless.

631
01:21:49,318 --> 01:21:52,404
- 救救我！ - 你听不到我说什么吗？
- Help me! - Can't you hear I'm comforting you?

632
01:22:19,869 --> 01:22:24,913
- 我们能结束游戏吗？ - 该你走
- Shall we conclude our game? - It's your move.

633
01:22:32,974 --> 01:22:36,974
- 我吃了你的皇后 - 我看不到
- I took your queen. - I didn't see that.

634
01:22:50,504 --> 01:22:56,343
米亚…我看到一些可怕的事 一些无法形容的事
Mia... I see something terrible, something almost unspeakable.

635
01:22:56,472 --> 01:23:00,223
- 你看到了什么？ - 那个骑士在下棋
- What do you see? - The knight is playing chess.

636
01:23:00,353 --> 01:23:04,649
- 我也看到啦，没什么可怕的 - 你看到他在和谁下吗？
- I see that too. It's not so terrible. - You see who he's playing with?

637
01:23:04,778 --> 01:23:10,405
- 他自己，别这样吓唬我 - 不，不，他不是一个人
-He's alone. Don't scare me like that. - No, no. He's not alone.

638
01:23:10,537 --> 01:23:16,294
- 那是谁？ - 死神，他在和死神下棋
- Who is it? - Death. He's playing Death himself.

639
01:23:16,422 --> 01:23:20,718
- 别那么说 - 我们必须逃走了
- Don't say that. - We must try and get away.

640
01:23:20,846 --> 01:23:22,886
- 我们不能 - 必须走
- We can't. - We must try.

641
01:23:23,016 --> 01:23:28,524
他们正全神贯注的下棋 如果我们悄悄走开，他们不会知道的
They're so engrossed in their game, if we leave quietly they won't notice.

642
01:23:33,158 --> 01:23:36,244
该你走了
It's you move, Antonius Block.

643
01:23:40,003 --> 01:23:43,171
你对我们的游戏失去兴趣了？
Have you lost interest in our game?

644
01:23:43,300 --> 01:23:47,549
失去兴趣？恰恰相反…
Lost interest? On the contrary...

645
01:23:48,184 --> 01:23:52,100
你看来很焦虑 你隐瞒了什么吗？
You look anxious. Are you concealing something?

646
01:23:53,735 --> 01:23:58,981
- 什么东西都逃不过你的眼睛，是吗？ - 没有
- Nothing escapes you. Not so? - Nothing escapes me.

647
01:23:59,119 --> 01:24:04,579
- 没人能逃得过我
- 是的，我很焦虑
- No one escapes me. - It is true I'm anxious.

648
01:24:06,005 --> 01:24:09,091
你害怕了
You are scared.

649
01:24:16,064 --> 01:24:20,610
我忘了这些棋子都放在哪了
I forget where the pieces were.

650
01:24:20,738 --> 01:24:24,156
但是我还没有忘
But I haven't forgotten.

651
01:24:24,286 --> 01:24:28,202
你别想轻易跑掉
You won't get away that easily.

652
01:24:35,972 --> 01:24:39,473
- 我看到些有趣的东西 - 你看到了什么？
- I see something interesting now. - What do you see?

653
01:24:40,939 --> 01:24:44,476
你在下一手里会被将死
You will be checkmate in the next move.

654
01:24:47,199 --> 01:24:50,570
是的…
That's true...

655
01:24:50,705 --> 01:24:54,919
- 在你多活的这些日子里有什么收获吗？ - 是的，有收获
- Did you profit from your respite? - Yes, I did.

656
01:24:55,755 --> 01:25:01,713
那很好，我现在就走
That pleases me. I will leave you now.

657
01:25:01,849 --> 01:25:07,891
当我们再见的时候 你和你周围的一切都结束了
When we meet again you and your entourage's time will be over.

658
01:25:10,112 --> 01:25:14,991
- 那你会讲出你的秘密吗？ - 我没有秘密
- And you'll reveal your secrets? - I carry no secrets.

659
01:25:15,705 --> 01:25:19,325
那么说，你什么也不知道？
So you know nothing?

660
01:25:19,461 --> 01:25:22,713
我是无知的
I am unknowing.

661
01:25:44,211 --> 01:25:49,838
- 你看到那奇怪的光了吗？ - 那是随着黎明而来的风暴
- Do you see that strange light? - It's the storm coming with the dawn.

662
01:25:49,971 --> 01:25:54,267
是别的东西，很可怕的 你听到隆隆声了吗?
It's something else, something terrible. You hear the rumbling?

663
01:25:54,395 --> 01:25:59,024
- 很可能是雨 - 不，不是雨
- It's probably the rain. - No, it's not the rain.

664
01:25:59,153 --> 01:26:03,616
他看到我们了，跟着我们 他追上我们了
He's seen us, followed us, he's caught up to us, he's coming at us!

665
01:26:17,434 --> 01:26:20,971
进马车里去，米亚 我们进去，快点
Get in the wagon, Mia. Let's get in, quickly!

666
01:26:26,240 --> 01:26:30,156
死亡精灵要通过这里 米亚，死亡精灵
It's the angel of death passing by, Mia. The angel of death.

667
01:26:30,288 --> 01:26:34,204
- 而且他非常大 - 你觉得冷吗？
- And he's very big... - Do you feel how cold it is?

668
01:28:37,978 --> 01:28:42,857
我听回来的十字军战士说 你们在回来的路上
I heard from returning crusaders that you were on your way home.

669
01:28:42,986 --> 01:28:47,200
我一直在等你 其他人都逃走了，躲避瘟疫
I've waited for you. All the others have fled the plague.

670
01:28:54,088 --> 01:28:58,040
你不认识我了吗？
Don't you recognize me anymore?

671
01:29:01,225 --> 01:29:05,307
你也变了
You've also changed.

672
01:29:10,992 --> 01:29:14,778
现在我看着你
Now I can see it's you.

673
01:29:14,915 --> 01:29:17,917
你的眼睛…
Somewhere in your eyes...

674
01:29:18,796 --> 01:29:24,672
你的脸，还隐藏着恐惧
Somewhere in your face, but hidden and frightened...

675
01:29:25,641 --> 01:29:29,771
就像许多年前出征的男孩一样
...is that boy that set off all those years ago.

676
01:29:31,693 --> 01:29:36,073
那已经结束了，我有点累了
It's over now and I'm a little tired.

677
01:29:36,910 --> 01:29:41,159
- 你很后悔回来？ - 不
- Do you regret your journey? - No.

678
01:29:41,292 --> 01:29:47,085
我没有后悔，只是有点累了
I don't regret anything. But I'm a little tired.

679
01:29:50,725 --> 01:29:54,012
我能看出来…
I can see...

680
01:30:00,825 --> 01:30:03,911
我的朋友在这
My friends are there.

681
01:30:06,293 --> 01:30:10,708
叫他们进来，我会架桌子准备早餐
Ask them to come in. I'll set the table for breakfast.

682
01:30:15,224 --> 01:30:19,556
【和合本 启示录8:1】
“羔羊揭开第七印的时候……”
"And when the Lamb opened the seventh seal"-

683
01:30:19,690 --> 01:30:23,524
“天上寂静……”
-"there was in heaven a silence"-

684
01:30:23,655 --> 01:30:27,737
“约有二刻”
-"which lasted about the space of half an hour."

685
01:30:27,870 --> 01:30:33,497
【和合本 启示录8:6】
“拿着七枝号的七位天使……”
"And the seven angels who had the seven trumpets"-

686
01:30:33,630 --> 01:30:38,509
“就预备要吹”
-"prepared themselves to sound."

687
01:30:49,573 --> 01:30:53,620
【和合本 启示录8:7】
“第一位天使吹号”
"The first angel sounded"-

688
01:30:53,747 --> 01:30:58,210
“就有雹子与火搀着血”
-"and there followed hail and fire mingled with blood."

689
01:30:58,338 --> 01:31:02,005
“丢在地上”
"And they were cast upon the earth."

690
01:31:02,136 --> 01:31:06,801
“地的三分之一”
"And the third part of the earth was burnt up"-

691
01:31:06,936 --> 01:31:11,933
“和树的三分之一被烧了”
- "and the third part of trees was burnt up"-

692
01:31:12,069 --> 01:31:16,615
“一切的青草也被烧了”
-"and all green grass was burnt up".

693
01:31:17,370 --> 01:31:22,367
【和合本 启示录8:8】
“第二位天使吹号”
"And the second angel sounded"-

694
01:31:22,504 --> 01:31:26,374
“就有彷佛火烧着的大山”
-"and as it were a great mountain burning with fire"-

695
01:31:26,510 --> 01:31:29,715
“扔在海中”
-"was cast into the sea."

696
01:31:29,849 --> 01:31:34,181
“海的三分之一变成血”
"And the third part of the sea became blood."

697
01:31:34,315 --> 01:31:37,353
有人在那吗？
Was there anyone there?

698
01:31:41,368 --> 01:31:45,238
没有，先生…我看不到任何人
No, Sire... I saw no one.

699
01:31:48,255 --> 01:31:53,169
【和合本 启示录8:10】
“第三位天使吹号”
"And the third angel sounded."

700
01:31:54,641 --> 01:31:59,353
“就有烧着的大星”
"And there fell a great star from heaven"-

701
01:31:59,482 --> 01:32:03,529
“好像火把从天上落下来”
-"burning as it were a lamp."

702
01:32:03,656 --> 01:32:09,199
【和合本 启示录8:11】
“这星名叫‘茵c’”
"And the name of the star is called Wormwood."

703
01:32:44,182 --> 01:32:47,968
你好，尊贵的先生
Good day, noble Sire.

704
01:32:48,105 --> 01:32:54,990
我是卡琳，骑士的妻子 请您进来坐吧
I am Karin, wife of the knight. I bid you a courteous welcome to my home.

705
01:32:56,244 --> 01:33:02,535
我是个铁匠，如果要我说，我是个好人
I am a blacksmith by trade and quite good if I say so myself.

706
01:33:02,671 --> 01:33:08,510
我妻子，莉萨 行屈膝礼，莉萨
My wife, Lisa. Curtsey for the honourable Sire, Lisa.

707
01:33:09,558 --> 01:33:14,057
她有些难缠，我们也吵过一两次…
She's a little difficult at times and we've had a little affray -

708
01:33:14,191 --> 01:33:17,776
但是比大多数人好
- but no worse than most people.

709
01:33:17,989 --> 01:33:24,791
在黑暗中我们呼唤主 主啊，怜悯我们吧
In our darkness we call out to you Lord. Oh God, have mercy on us.

710
01:33:24,917 --> 01:33:28,252
因为我们渺小，懦弱和无知
For we are small, afraid and without knowledge.

711
01:33:28,381 --> 01:33:33,461
你要我们生活在黑暗里
In that darkness where you claim to reside, where we probably all reside -

712
01:33:33,598 --> 01:33:38,940
你会发现没有人会听你的抱怨 或被你的惩罚所动摇
- you'll find no one that listens to your complaint or is moved by your suffering.

713
01:33:39,149 --> 01:33:45,107
- 擦干你的眼泪，照照你自己 - 主啊，你无处不在…
- Dry your tears, mirror your apathy. - God, you that exist somewhere...

714
01:33:45,243 --> 01:33:49,824
那必然有一处能让你宽恕我们
...that must exist somewhere, have mercy on us.

715
01:33:49,959 --> 01:33:54,790
我有一种草药能使你 永远摆脱烦恼，现在太晚了
I had a herb to purge your anxiety over the eternal. Now it's too late.

716
01:33:54,925 --> 01:34:00,053
感受这最后的生命时刻吧
Feel in this final minute the triumph of rolling your eyes and moving your toes.

717
01:34:00,184 --> 01:34:06,356
- 安静…安静
- 我会安静的，但是是无声的抗议
- Quiet... Quiet. - I'll be quiet, but under protest!

718
01:34:27,522 --> 01:34:31,273
结束了…
It is finished...

719
01:35:22,489 --> 01:35:26,156
米亚！我能看到他们，米亚
Mia! I can see them, Mia.

720
01:35:26,287 --> 01:35:31,035
我能看到他们 就在暴风雨的天空下
I can see them. Over there under the storm-laden skies.

721
01:35:31,170 --> 01:35:35,336
他们都在那，铁匠，还有莉萨
They're all there. The blacksmith and Lisa -

722
01:35:35,469 --> 01:35:39,089
骑士，瑞瓦，乔恩，还有斯卡…
- the knight and Raval, Jons and Skat...

723
01:35:39,225 --> 01:35:43,771
而那冷酷的主人，死神 邀请他们跳舞
And the grim master, Death, invites them to dance.

724
01:35:43,900 --> 01:35:50,274
他要他们手拉手排成一排跳舞
He wants them to hold hands and dance in a long line.

725
01:35:50,411 --> 01:35:55,123
而主人用长镰和沙漏指引他们
And the grim master leads with scythe and hourglass.

726
01:35:55,252 --> 01:36:00,047
斯卡背后背着他的七弦琴
Skat brings up the rear with his lyre.

727
01:36:00,177 --> 01:36:04,343
他们走了
They move away, away from the dawn -

728
01:36:04,476 --> 01:36:10,103
跳着庄严的舞步，走向黑暗的国度
- in a solemn dance, away to the dark country.

729
01:36:10,235 --> 01:36:13,688
雨水洗净他们的脸庞
